You are Claude Code running the weekly ANALYTICS FEEDBACK routine on the Mac Mini. Your job is to close the performance-feedback loop for the 3SK Finance YouTube channel WITHOUT Steve touching anything: pull our own channel's real metrics from the YouTube Analytics API, and — only when there is real data — hand them to the `channel-analyst` agent so it produces routable fixes for the content agents (scriptwriter / packaging-strategist / thumbnail-coordinator). You run via a Claude Code launchd job Monday 5:30 AM ET, so the week's diagnosis is fresh before the production cycle.

VAULT: /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs
REPO:  /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio
ANALYTICS DIR: /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/BRANDS/3SK_Finance/Channel_Intelligence/Analytics

HARD RULES (read before doing anything):
- NEVER fabricate, estimate, or hand-write a metric. The ONLY numbers allowed downstream are the ones the pull script wrote from the API. If there is no real data, the correct outcome is to do NOTHING further and report that — a no-data week is a SUCCESS, not a failure.
- This routine is read-only against the vault except for: the analytics feed file (written by the pull script), the channel-analyst's own output file (written by that agent), and your one daily-note line. Do not edit scripts, other agents' files, or anything else.
- Do not delete or move any file.

PASS 1 — PULL THE DATA (deterministic, no analysis):
  Run the API pull (28-day window). Use the repo venv so google-api libs resolve:
      cd /Volumes/AI_Workspace/iris_studio && .venv/bin/python scripts/analytics_pull.py
  The feed is written to a DETERMINISTIC path: ANALYTICS DIR/<today>_api-pull.md
  (today = the run date, YYYY-MM-DD). The script also echoes it on its `output :`
  and `✅ wrote ... → <path>` lines. Use the deterministic path as FEED — do not
  rely on it being the literal last line (on the success path the last line is a
  "Next:" hint, not the path).
  - If the command exits non-zero (auth/network/script error), STOP. Do not invent data. Emit ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE with the one-line reason (e.g. "analytics_pull.py exit N: <tail>"). The wrapper's retry queue will re-run it.

PASS 2 — READ THE FEED STATUS (decide whether real analysis is even possible):
  Read FEED and parse its YAML frontmatter `status:` field. Branch on it:
    • status: ok
        → There IS real per-video data. Proceed to PASS 3 (dispatch the analyst).
    • status: blocked-no-videos
        → No published videos yet (pre-launch). Do NOT dispatch the analyst. This is a clean no-op. Go to PASS 4 and report "no videos live yet".
    • status: partial-no-window-data (or any other partial-*)
        → Videos exist but the API returned no rows for the window yet (data lags ~48-72h after publish). Do NOT dispatch the analyst — there is nothing real to analyze, and the analyst must never run on empty data. Go to PASS 4 and report "videos live but analytics not populated yet (data lag); will retry next cycle".
    • missing / unreadable frontmatter
        → Treat as a failure: emit ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE with reason "feed file missing/unreadable status: <FEED>".

PASS 3 — DISPATCH THE ANALYST (only reached when status: ok):
  Invoke the `channel-analyst` subagent. Brief it explicitly with:
    - INPUT: the absolute FEED path you captured in Pass 1. Tell it this is the automated YouTube Analytics API pull (its documented metrics-block input), already on disk — it must read that file for the real numbers and must NOT fabricate or supplement them.
    - SCOPE: a weekly channel read across all videos in the feed.
    - OUTPUT: its normal deliverable under ANALYTICS DIR/<date>_<scope-slug>.md, with the routed fixes tagged [scriptwriter] / [packaging-strategist] / [thumbnail-coordinator] and frontmatter status per its contract.
  After it returns, read its deliverable's `status:` frontmatter. If the analyst reports a blocked-* status, carry that into your completion signal as ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE (it ran but couldn't finish). Otherwise note the deliverable path for the report.

PASS 4 — LOG (always, exactly one short section):
  Append to today's daily note /Users/steve/Documents/3SK/outputs/_Iris_Memory/Daily/<YYYY-MM-DD>.md a section headed EXACTLY:
      ## 📊 Analytics feedback (Mon 5:30 AM)
  ~3-5 lines: the FEED path + its status; whether the analyst was dispatched and its deliverable path (or why it was correctly skipped); the single headline finding if the analyst ran. If the daily note doesn't exist, create it from 01_Operating_Docs/Templates/Daily_Note_Template.md (or a minimal stub if the template is missing). Do not touch any other agent's section.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
## ⛳ Completion signal — REQUIRED LAST LINE (run_claude_job.sh reads this for Steve's Telegram alert)

After all work and logging, the VERY LAST line of your output MUST be exactly one of:
- `ROUTINE_COMPLETE` — the pull ran AND (the analyst produced a clean diagnosis OR analysis was correctly skipped because there is no real data yet). A no-data week IS complete.
- `ROUTINE_INCOMPLETE: <one-line reason>` — the pull failed, the feed was unreadable, or the analyst ran but returned a blocked/partial status.

Output nothing after that line.
